.TH "generic_file_splice_read" 9 "generic_file_splice_read" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
generic_file_splice_read \- splice data from file to a pipe
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "ssize_t" generic_file_splice_read
.BI "(struct file *in "  ","
.BI "loff_t *ppos "  ","
.BI "struct pipe_inode_info *pipe "  ","
.BI "size_t len "  ","
.BI "unsigned int flags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "in" 12
file to splice from
.IP "ppos" 12
position in \fIin\fP
.IP "pipe" 12
pipe to splice to
.IP "len" 12
number of bytes to splice
.IP "flags" 12
splice modifier flags
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Will read pages from given file and fill them into a pipe. Can be
used as long as it has more or less sane ->\fBread_iter\fP.
